Commented on #29 Make `check` mutable in `TaskImpl` + add `task!()` macro

Ok, I can move the chase.rs and adding macros to separate PRs then, since they're unrelated to this issue. 👍 Regarding mutating the world within tasks, both on_enter and on_exit are insufficient because they provide a closure of Fn(Entity, Commands) . With Commands , you cannot mutate resources, mutate fields in components, etc. Given that the check function is parsed as a System function, that gives us access to Query<> , Res<> and other parameter types that give us access to various parts of the world. However since check is a read-only system, we can't use Query<&mut ...> or ResMut<> to mutate the world. Even if on_enter and on_exit are parsed as a System function, that still won't handle the case where a task needs to update a component with new data it just received after the task has already started, but before the task has exited.
Fix wander and chase AI, add account in use check
